I'd better get going.

25:18.750 --> 25:21.275
Thank you very much for the vinegar.

25:41.673 --> 25:44.301
Where's Branca? She jump ship already?

25:45.176 --> 25:48.009
She's in hospital for a while. Cyst.

25:51.149 --> 25:53.982
Where's the old fart? I gotta talk to him.

25:54.319 --> 25:57.413
It's his afternoon nap.
You want me to wake him?

25:59.157 --> 26:00.749
Give him a while.

26:03.395 --> 26:06.626
Want some wine?
From Furio's uncle in Italy?

26:13.104 --> 26:15.629
He says they had a lot of sun in this year.

26:16.875 --> 26:17.842
<i>Salute.</i>

26:23.415 --> 26:24.882
It needs ice.

26:31.456 --> 26:33.549
I'm going to watch the Bloomberg.

26:41.933 --> 26:45.460
- What's all that?
- I'm making a website for my business.

26:47.305 --> 26:48.932
You know how to do that?

26:49.007 --> 26:51.271
I'm going to pay somebody...

26:51.810 --> 26:55.075
$35 an hour? I stuck, I call Bill.

26:56.581 --> 26:58.378
You got married yet?

26:58.617 --> 27:02.075
Maybe when he gets back
from Port St. Lucie.

27:02.921 --> 27:05.412
The baseball spring training for his Mets.

27:08.693 --> 27:10.456
That Bill's a lucky man.

27:12.430 --> 27:16.366
You Russians, you got all the angles,
you come over here, you bust your ass.

27:16.434 --> 27:17.833
People are people.

27:20.205 --> 27:23.732
Look at you.
You got every excuse to be in the bottle...

27:23.875 --> 27:26.537
and here you are designing websites.

27:27.679 --> 27:29.613
What do you mean? What excuse?

27:31.483 --> 27:33.815
- Your...
- No, what?

27:35.654 --> 27:37.645
Come on, you know, that...

27:38.189 --> 27:39.383
My leg.

27:40.425 --> 27:41.756
Of course.

27:42.160 --> 27:44.458
I don't think of it right away.

27:48.733 --> 27:50.223
There are worse things.

27:50.301 --> 27:52.895
<i>...digital countdown timer
with automatic shut-off.</i>

27:52.971 --> 27:55.997
<i>Simply put your food in
and set the timer, walk away.</i>

27:56.074 --> 27:58.702
<i>Your new George Foreman Gril
wil tel you exactly...</i>

27:58.777 --> 28:01.507
<i>when your food is griled to perfection.</i>

28:01.880 --> 28:03.905
<i>This gril does al the work for you.</i>

28:03.982 --> 28:07.782
<i>With my exclusive 20-minute
digital countdown timer with auto...</i>

28:08.253 --> 28:10.653
Heroin, you got only one option.

28:10.755 --> 28:15.249
A dog you love catches rabies,
you put her out of its misery, Anthony.

28:18.697 --> 28:19.686
<i>Salute.</i>

28:31.476 --> 28:33.205
So what do I do, Uncle Jun'?

28:33.278 --> 28:36.907
The feds get him in his condition,
who knows what he's liable to say.

28:37.248 --> 28:39.808
You go on trial, like me,
you won't sleep at night.

28:39.884 --> 28:42.079
All the more reason to clean him up.

28:46.024 --> 28:47.548
Still, he's...

28:48.259 --> 28:51.319
He's a major liability.
If it were anybody else...

28:54.299 --> 28:56.597
It reminds me of people's feet.

29:01.005 --> 29:03.838
I don't know if I can do that other thing.

29:04.509 --> 29:06.602
Dominic Palladino, do you remember him?

29:06.678 --> 29:09.647
- B&E guy, a real juicer.
- He's in AA now.

29:09.981 --> 29:12.575
I thought maybe I'd give him a call.

29:13.551 --> 29:15.451
They can treat this shit nowadays.

29:15.520 --> 29:19.081
Me with the competency hearings.
You with the head shrinkers.

29:19.190 --> 29:20.589
This one in rehab now.

29:26.931 --> 29:30.094
I was so upset when he didn't bring me
a present back from Italy.

29:30.168 --> 29:32.363
He got something for A.J. And for Meadow.

29:32.971 --> 29:36.202
He gave me some vinegar,
but I don't think it was meant for me.

29:36.274 --> 29:38.572
It must've meant something, that he felt bad.

29:38.643 --> 29:41.203
Carmela, you sound like you're 15 years old.

29:41.279 --> 29:43.543
I say I'm helping him decorate.

29:43.615 --> 29:46.140
I bring A.J. With me.
Now even he smells a rat.

29:47.118 --> 29:50.952
If Tony suspects one iota,
you know what'll happen to Furio.

29:51.022 --> 29:54.014
These guys are living in a different century.

29:54.225 --> 29:56.853
- It didn't stop you.
- Steve at the gym?

29:58.096 --> 30:01.395
I felt so guilty all the time.
The lies and the sneaking.

30:02.033 --> 30:05.093
It took Jackie going in the hospital
to get me to stop.

30:06.337 --> 30:09.500
- We haven't slept together yet.
- You're not fucking him?

30:09.974 --> 30:12.067
So this isn't really real.

30:13.144 --> 30:14.338
It is real.

30:15.446 --> 30:16.970
We communicate.

30:17.382 --> 30:19.816
He looks at me like I'm beautiful.

30:20.018 --> 30:22.578
He thinks I'm interesting when I talk.

30:23.121 --> 30:27.023
Just those few minutes
when we see each other, I live for those.

30:28.393 --> 30:32.557
I feel like my life is slipping through
my fingers and I will never be happy.

30:32.831 --> 30:35.629
If you haven't slept with him yet, don't.

30:35.733 --> 30:37.894
And don't go over there anymore.

30:52.750 --> 30:54.047
We're all here?

30:55.553 --> 30:56.645
Good afternoon.

30:56.721 --> 30:59.281
For those of you who don't know me,
I am Dominic...

30:59.357 --> 31:01.291
and I'm an alcoholic and an addict.

31:01.359 --> 31:03.224
Don't forget "scumbag. "

31:04.395 --> 31:06.420
As some of you obviously don't know...

31:06.497 --> 31:09.364
I've also been in recovery now
going on four years.

31:09.868 --> 31:13.235
I joined AA in prison,
and frankly, it saved my life.

31:14.706 --> 31:18.301
Okay, now, we're all here today
because we have one thing in common.

31:18.376 --> 31:21.743
Not only do we share
a certain background and culture...

31:21.813 --> 31:25.374
we care about Chris and want to help him
with his heroin addiction.

31:26.150 --> 31:29.210
Any one of you been involved
in an intervention before?

31:37.762 --> 31:40.595
Caught our daughter
smoking pot once, but...

31:40.665 --> 31:42.496
- Not really, no.
- No problem.

31:42.700 --> 31:45.692
An intervention
is a non-judgmental confrontation.

31:47.071 --> 31:49.369
A "care-frontation," we call it.

31:49.841 --> 31:53.242
Now, what I need from you guys
is to make a list of specific times...

31:53.311 --> 31:56.109
where Christopher's drug use
impacted on you directly.

31:58.516 --> 32:00.484
For example, Adriana, is it?

32:01.619 --> 32:03.519
You would say something like this:

32:03.588 --> 32:06.921
"Christopher, last Monday you came home
from work high...

32:06.991 --> 32:10.119
"and belligerent,
and you were physically abusive to me. "

32:11.296 --> 32:13.526
What if he's high when we try to talk to him?

32:13.631 --> 32:15.258
Then we wait till he's sober.

32:15.400 --> 32:18.927
My first intervention, Steven Patrano
waited 10 hours for me to sober up.

32:19.003 --> 32:22.461
- Your first intervention?
- In 1997, I suffered a relapse.

32:22.674 --> 32:26.906
As in heroin addiction, alcoholics
suffer a fairly high recidivism rate.

32:27.211 --> 32:30.510
Great. So he's taking advice
from a two-time loser.

32:31.349 --> 32:33.544
There are no losers in recovery.

32:35.019 --> 32:37.544
Actually, I never really met Ralph's kid.

32:37.989 --> 32:40.389
I saw him once from a distance, though.

32:40.692 --> 32:41.886
Handsome boy.

32:43.428 --> 32:46.864
He's got a long struggle ahead of him,
that's for sure.

32:47.265 --> 32:48.789
Doctors, rehab...

32:49.467 --> 32:51.094
physical therapy...

32:53.738 --> 32:56.901
I think I'm going to have
the medallions of veal.

33:11.089 --> 33:13.853
You make me late for a table
at Tavern on the fucking Green?

33:13.925 --> 33:15.825
How's the real estate business?

33:15.893 --> 33:17.690
- Excuse me?
- You know, HUD.

33:17.962 --> 33:21.090
Garside Street, you, Ralph, Zellman.

33:22.333 --> 33:24.198
Zellman tell you this?

33:25.503 --> 33:28.404
Carmine doesn't know anything
about this yet.

33:28.639 --> 33:31.699
I'm giving you an opportunity to cut a deal,
make it right.

33:31.776 --> 33:35.644
Last time, Frelinghuysen Avenue, I cut you
in out of friendship, but that's over.

33:35.713 --> 33:38.375
You got nothing coming to you.
You or Carmine.

33:39.784 --> 33:42.150
You sure you want to go down this road?

34:01.105 --> 34:04.506
How much to paint a different suit on him,
change his face a little?

34:04.575 --> 34:06.805
- Pardon me?
- Why throw it away?

34:07.545 --> 34:09.137
A stronger chin, maybe.

34:09.414 --> 34:12.110
I was thinking like those paintings
in the courthouse.

34:12.183 --> 34:15.983
Something classy, you know,
like a Revolutionary War general.

34:16.353 --> 34:18.844
Napoleon and his horse. That kind of thing.

34:19.424 --> 34:21.858
He's rather portly to be Napoleon.

34:22.159 --> 34:23.956
Not Napoleon, exactly.

34:24.795 --> 34:26.058
Like Napoleon.

34:29.534 --> 34:31.024
Sit down. Relax.

34:36.107 --> 34:37.835
What's going on, Ton'?

34:39.577 --> 34:42.808
I think I know what happened to Ralph,
and if I'm right...

34:43.081 --> 34:44.605
he ain't coming back.

34:49.219 --> 34:51.313
- It was New York.
- Johnny Sack?

34:51.755 --> 34:53.656
What was it? The fat joke?

34:54.092 --> 34:55.821
I'm sure that didn't help.

34:56.260 --> 34:57.318
Carmine.

34:58.596 --> 35:01.224
This HUD thing we're into,
they wanted a piece of it.

35:01.299 --> 35:03.324
I think they confronted Ralph...

35:03.968 --> 35:06.334
- things went sour.
- What'd he say, John?

35:06.504 --> 35:09.098
Wasn't what he said so much
as what he didn't say.

35:09.173 --> 35:11.004
We're talking about New York here.

35:11.075 --> 35:13.976
Before we do anything
in terms of a payback...

35:14.812 --> 35:16.336
you go to your people.

35:16.481 --> 35:18.346
I want a full investigation.

35:19.117 --> 35:22.109
Nobody makes a move
until we know what happened.

35:22.487 --> 35:23.784
You understand?

35:28.493 --> 35:29.755
What the fuck?

35:33.397 --> 35:35.331
- What's going on?
- Have a seat.

35:37.768 --> 35:40.168
I'm Dominic.
I know you don't know me, but...

35:40.404 --> 35:43.396
You're the guy who broke into
Stew Leonard's that time.

35:43.474 --> 35:45.408
You stole all those pork loins.

35:46.277 --> 35:49.007
Yeah, but that's not why I'm here today.

35:50.615 --> 35:53.607
- We're here to talk about your drug problem.
- What?

35:54.986 --> 35:58.353
- Jesus Christ, you fucking kidding me?
- Sorry, baby, please.

35:59.690 --> 36:01.157
No, fuck this shit.

36:01.325 --> 36:03.486
You were told once. Now, sit down.

36:05.229 --> 36:06.491
Sit down.

36:19.243 --> 36:21.609
Ma? Jesus.

36:28.486 --> 36:30.351
This won't be easy for any of us.

36:30.421 --> 36:34.289
But I want you to know that we're here today
because we care about you.

36:34.759 --> 36:38.251
- What was this, your idea?
- All we ask is that you listen.

36:41.332 --> 36:43.425
Adriana, you want to begin?

36:50.708 --> 36:52.869
"Christopher, I love you very much.

36:53.578 --> 36:56.547
"My only dream is that
we have a happy life together.

36:56.881 --> 37:00.009
"The last few months,
things have got very bad with us...

37:00.117 --> 37:02.517
"because of you using drugs all the time.

37:03.054 --> 37:06.717
- "You're high all the time and I can't take it. "
- Be specific, hon.

37:09.493 --> 37:13.054
"When we first started going out,
we made love all the time.

37:13.764 --> 37:17.291
- "Now, because of the drugs... "
- Jesus, is this fucking necessary?

37:17.368 --> 37:18.392
Go ahead.

37:19.337 --> 37:21.737
"... you can no longer function as a man.

37:23.474 --> 37:27.035
"Last week when I came home
to learn that you had killed our dog...

37:27.144 --> 37:28.941
"that was the final straw. "

37:31.015 --> 37:33.916
You killed the dog? What'd you do that for?

37:34.318 --> 37:36.411
- It was an accident.
- Was it barking?

37:36.487 --> 37:38.921
He sat on her while he was high.

37:39.257 --> 37:41.691
- Jesus Christ.
- I fell asleep.

37:42.226 --> 37:44.251
She got suffocated or something.

37:47.265 --> 37:49.130
Are you done, Adriana?

37:54.138 --> 37:55.605
You killed little Cosette?

37:55.673 --> 37:58.198
I ought to suffocate you, you little prick!

37:58.309 --> 38:00.106
Tony, we're going in order.

38:01.379 --> 38:03.404
"When I came in to open up one morning...

38:03.481 --> 38:08.077
"you had your head half in the toilet.
Your hair was in the toilet water.

38:08.386 --> 38:10.786
- "Disgusting. "
- I told you, I had the flu.

38:10.988 --> 38:13.923
- I said my piece.
- Great, I can't even defend myself, now?

38:13.991 --> 38:16.960
- No one's attacking you.
- It doesn't change anything.

38:18.029 --> 38:20.998
But I can verify that he was sick
for a little while.

38:21.499 --> 38:24.434
This thing with the dog.
How could you not see it on the chair?

38:24.502 --> 38:25.867
You're getting emotional.

38:25.936 --> 38:28.803
That's because I know what it's like
to lose a pet!

38:32.510 --> 38:35.968
I happen to know that you were high
at my mother-in-law's wake.

38:36.213 --> 38:40.479
You were talking non-stop for 20 minutes,
nothing but gibberish.

38:40.751 --> 38:42.378
My mother's wake.

38:43.054 --> 38:44.385
Jesus Christ.

38:50.895 --> 38:53.989
- You want to read your statement?
- I don't write nothing down.

38:54.065 --> 38:56.192
So I'll keep this short and sweet.

38:56.334 --> 38:58.461
You're weak. You're out of control.

38:58.636 --> 39:01.605
You've become an embarrassment
to yourself and everybody else.

39:01.672 --> 39:03.572
- Listen to you.
- Guys.

39:04.175 --> 39:06.405
We said "non-judgmental. "

39:06.711 --> 39:08.975
Fuck that. Let him take his medicine.

39:09.146 --> 39:11.706
Seriously, you want to talk
about fucking up?

39:11.849 --> 39:13.578
- Watch it, Chrissy.
- What?

39:13.784 --> 39:15.615
I thought we're being honest here.

39:16.787 --> 39:19.779
You got some balls, you know that.
All of you.

39:21.192 --> 39:24.423
You want to talk about self-control,
how about you, Sil?

39:24.662 --> 39:28.359
Fucking every slut working in the place
when you got a wife and kids.

39:30.234 --> 39:31.496
Or you, Paulie.

39:31.569 --> 39:34.367
Remember last winter in the woods
with the Russian guy?

39:34.438 --> 39:35.871
I am warning you!

39:35.940 --> 39:38.306
There he goes, Mr. Type A personality.

39:38.376 --> 39:41.106
We're talking about
you killing yourself with drugs!

39:41.178 --> 39:42.668
Not my fucking personality!

39:42.747 --> 39:44.681
- Right.
- I'm going to kill myself?

39:44.749 --> 39:47.582
The way you eat,
you'll have a heart attack before you're 50.

39:47.651 --> 39:49.812
- Sit down.
- You're talking to the boss.

39:49.887 --> 39:52.913
Good, maybe someone will smack
some goddamn sense into him!

39:52.990 --> 39:55.823
Great, my own mother.
Fuck you, you fucking whore!

39:56.694 --> 39:57.991
Son of a bitch!

40:00.631 --> 40:01.962
Guys, please!

40:02.032 --> 40:03.465
Come on!

40:04.101 --> 40:05.090
Stop it!

40:11.876 --> 40:13.901
Excuse me. How's he doing?

40:14.512 --> 40:16.036
I'm a relative.

40:16.113 --> 40:19.480
He slipped off the kitchen counter
spraying for ants?

40:19.617 --> 40:21.141
He was wearing socks.

40:21.986 --> 40:25.251
- Are you aware that he has a drug problem?
- Really?

40:26.524 --> 40:30.790
The man has a hairline skull fracture.
We'll admit him, keep him overnight.

40:31.762 --> 40:32.888
One minute.

40:36.634 --> 40:38.261
Give us a minute, okay?

40:49.914 --> 40:51.381
Does it hurt?

40:52.383 --> 40:54.476
They gave me some aspirin.

40:56.053 --> 40:59.181
Enjoy it, because it's the last fucking drug
you'll ever take.

41:01.892 --> 41:05.089
- I'm sorry, T.
- Shut the fuck up and listen to me.

41:06.664 --> 41:10.065
You're my nephew, Christopher,
and I love you.

41:11.969 --> 41:14.403
That's the only reason
you're alive right now.

41:14.472 --> 41:17.168
If it were anybody else, anybody...

41:17.541 --> 41:21.238
they would've had their intervention
through the back of their head.

41:21.912 --> 41:24.107
You and me, we're close.

41:25.149 --> 41:27.344
We've done a lot of things for each other.

41:27.418 --> 41:29.386
That cop shot my father.

41:31.121 --> 41:33.851
I know what you're telling me,
I'll never forget that.

41:33.924 --> 41:35.391
This is how you repay me.

41:35.459 --> 41:38.656
I gotta worry if you'll flip
over a nickel bag of white powder.

41:38.729 --> 41:41.095
- No, Tony, never.
- You lied to me.

41:41.298 --> 41:45.462
I told you, you were the future of this family.
I gave you that responsibility.

41:45.536 --> 41:48.596
And you looked me in the eye,
and you accepted it...

41:48.672 --> 41:50.731
and you were fucking high.

41:53.611 --> 41:54.873
Shut up.

41:56.247 --> 42:00.308
Tomorrow morning I gotta go with Patsy
up to this rehab place in Pennsylvania.

42:00.384 --> 42:02.375
You're going in. You're staying in.

42:02.453 --> 42:05.684
You'll go to every session,
and you'll keep your mouth shut.

42:05.756 --> 42:08.748
Now, if you need anything, anything at all...

42:10.160 --> 42:13.152
Patsy's going to be
half a mile away from you...

42:13.697 --> 42:15.062
in a motel.

42:17.201 --> 42:19.999
Do you understand what I'm saying to you?

42:21.772 --> 42:24.297
- Do you understand?
- Tony, I'm sorry!

42:29.480 --> 42:31.710
How did I fucking get to this?

42:41.992 --> 42:44.825
- So he comes again.
- Brought some pastries.

42:45.329 --> 42:47.058
- Is he taking a nap?
- Yeah.

42:47.731 --> 42:50.894
- Is he driving you to drink?
- I can drive myself.

43:14.458 --> 43:15.948
I needed that.

43:16.694 --> 43:18.093
What's the matter?

43:18.228 --> 43:21.220
Spent a long time in the hospital last night.

43:22.600 --> 43:25.000
The shit that goes on down there.

43:28.138 --> 43:30.265
I wasn't expecting visitors.

43:44.521 --> 43:46.318
How about those Mets?

43:46.957 --> 43:49.118
Don't start with me and those Mets.

43:57.001 --> 43:59.128
You know, I was thinking about you.

44:00.604 --> 44:02.572
- So you're drunk already.
- No.

44:02.640 --> 44:04.437
I was thinking about the way you are.

44:04.508 --> 44:08.604
How you always have this little smile,
like you got your own private joke.

44:13.517 --> 44:15.348
You don't talk much, do you?

44:21.992 --> 44:23.516
I wish I knew your secret.

44:23.594 --> 44:26.791
Lose a leg and start making websites.

44:28.132 --> 44:32.466
That's the whole purpose for people
like me, to inspire people like you.

44:36.073 --> 44:39.770
- Jesus, no offense.
- That's the trouble with you Americans.

44:40.077 --> 44:42.807
You expect nothing bad ever to happen...

44:43.080 --> 44:46.345
when the rest of the world expects
only bad to happen.

44:46.417 --> 44:49.716
- They're not disappointed.
- That's a fucking grim outlook.

44:50.354 --> 44:53.255
You have everything, and still you complain.

44:53.724 --> 44:56.659
You lie on couches
and bitch to your psychiatrist.

44:57.995 --> 45:00.486
You got too much time
to think about yourselves.

45:00.564 --> 45:02.589
Sounds like me all right.

45:04.334 --> 45:05.767
You're not so bad.

45:06.637 --> 45:08.832
You have many fine qualities.

45:09.106 --> 45:11.734
You are big and strong...

45:12.543 --> 45:15.011
full of life, mischief.

45:15.679 --> 45:18.147
I have always feel positive towards you.

45:22.753 --> 45:24.584
You should see yourself now...

45:25.856 --> 45:29.121
in the shadows there,
with the smoke all around you.

45:31.095 --> 45:34.587
You're beautiful.
You remind me of that movie star...

45:36.166 --> 45:38.327
- Irina is beautiful.
- Greta Garbo.

46:39.129 --> 46:40.994
- May I help you?
- Yeah.

46:44.902 --> 46:47.837
<i>Brad to reception, your 1:00 client is here.</i>

46:51.842 --> 46:53.139
You'll call me later?

46:53.210 --> 46:56.111
No phone calls for the first two weeks.
House rules.

46:59.850 --> 47:01.078
I'll write.

47:01.618 --> 47:04.519
I was thinking of keeping a journal anyway.

47:04.922 --> 47:07.413
Get it published, maybe,
under my pen name.

47:12.029 --> 47:13.394
Congratulations.

47:15.332 --> 47:18.267
You got here, dude. That's the hardest part.

47:19.803 --> 47:22.067
I'm going to have to search your bag.

47:28.278 --> 47:31.076
- Cigarettes are okay, right?
- Cigarettes are fine.

47:31.148 --> 47:35.642
